==Japanese==

===Etymology===
From {{term|す|su|do}}. As with all verbs, during Middle Japanese the [[終止形|conclusive]] was gradually replaced by the [[連体形|attributive]], realigning the conjugations.

===Verb===
{{ja-verb|h|type=3|kanji=為る|rom=suru}}
# to [[do]]
#: [[何]]を'''して'''いますか。
#::[[なに]]を'''して'''いますか。
#::''Nani o '''shite'''imasu ka?''
#:::What are you '''doing'''?
# to [[wear]] (accessories)
#: [[ネクタイ]]を'''する'''。
#:: [[ねくたい]]を'''する'''。
#:: ''[[nekutai|Nekutai]] o '''suru'''.''
#::: To '''wear''' a [[necktie]].

====Usage notes====
* The verb する is seldom written in kanji (為る).
* It is common to use する after certain nouns to indicate that the noun is being done; this is ''highly'' productive, meaning many verbs can be derived from nouns in this way, comparable to English {{term|-ly}}:
*: [[失礼]] ([[shitsurei]], "rudeness") → [[失礼する|失礼'''する''']] ([[shitsurei suru|shitsurei '''suru''']], "to commit a rudeness → to be rude")
*: [[旅行]] ([[ryokō]], "journey") → [[旅行する|旅行'''する''']] ([[ryokō suru|ryokō '''suru''']], "to travel")

